					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I've given this some thought, an although an AVR is running at far greater clock speeds than the GB bus, (don't even consider Arduino) You will need logic doing your switching as the gameboy expects the data to be on the bus almost the same time as the /RD is asserted. If you were given 1 GB clock cycle to have it prepared then an AVR will get the job done, but that is not what the gameboy is asking. AVR + Logic Yes, AVR alone, no.</div>

