					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Maybe if you were to use one of the arduino Mega's? It has an Xbus interface. Not too familiar with it, but perhaps it could monitor your data and address bus along with control signals? All just ideas. How about burning an EEPROM with a bit mask which sits on the address bus and generates outputs on its data bus when reads/writes to particular addresses are made. Use these outputs to latch registers. You could have a very complicated, narrow set of addresses that trigger certain functions.</div>

